{
  "page": "Jonquil Darke",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Darke\" title=\"House Darke\"><img alt=\"None.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/5/58/None.svg/50px-None.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/5/58/None.svg/75px-None.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/5/58/None.svg/100px-None.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\">Jonquil Darke<br /><span style=\"font-size:80%;font-weight:normal\"> the Scarlet Shadow</span></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Darke\" title=\"House Darke\"><img alt=\"None.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/5/58/None.svg/50px-None.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/5/58/None.svg/75px-None.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/5/58/None.svg/100px-None.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Jonquil_Darke_by_Amuelia.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Jonquil Darke by Amuelia.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/5/51/Jonquil_Darke_by_Amuelia.png/350px-Jonquil_Darke_by_Amuelia.png\" width=\"350\" height=\"382\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/5/51/Jonquil_Darke_by_Amuelia.png/525px-Jonquil_Darke_by_Amuelia.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/5/51/Jonquil_Darke_by_Amuelia.png/700px-Jonquil_Darke_by_Amuelia.png 2x\" /></a><div>Jonquil Darke by Amuelia</div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Aliases</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li>The Serpent in Scarlet<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li><li>The Scarlet Shadow<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabbirth.2C_death_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabbirth.2C_death_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiances</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Darke\" title=\"House Darke\">House Darke</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Darklyn\" title=\"House Darklyn\">House Darklyn</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">House Targaryen</a></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Crownlands\" title=\"Crownlands\">Crownlands</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Father</th><td>\nLord <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Darklyn_(father_of_Jonquil_Darke)\" title=\"Lord Darklyn (father of Jonquil Darke)\">Darklyn</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Books</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Rise_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"The Rise of the Dragon\">The Rise of the Dragon</a></i> (mentioned)</li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Jonquil Darke</b>, known as the <b>Scarlet Shadow</b>, was a noblewoman from <a href=\"/index.php/House_Darke\" title=\"House Darke\">House Darke</a>, born a <a href=\"/index.php/Bastard\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bastard\">bastard</a> daughter of <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Darklyn_(father_of_Jonquil_Darke)\" title=\"Lord Darklyn (father of Jonquil Darke)\">Lord Darklyn</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Duskendale\" title=\"Duskendale\">Duskendale</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Jonquil_Darke&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>At the <a href=\"/index.php/Golden_Wedding\" title=\"Golden Wedding\">Golden Wedding</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/49_AC\" title=\"49 AC\">49&#160;AC</a>, a test of arms that became known as the <a href=\"/index.php/War_for_the_White_Cloaks\" title=\"War for the White Cloaks\">War for the White Cloaks</a> was held, with hundreds of <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knights</a> competing for the honor of serving in the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\">Kingsguard</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Jaehaerys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Jaehaerys I Targaryen\">Jaehaerys I Targaryen</a>. Jonquil took part as a slender <a href=\"/index.php/Mystery_knight\" title=\"Mystery knight\">mystery knight</a> known as the <i><a href=\"/index.php/Serpent\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Serpent\">Serpent</a> in Scarlet</i>. She was eventually defeated and unmasked, and became a great favorite with the <a href=\"/index.php/Smallfolk\" title=\"Smallfolk\">smallfolk</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In <a href=\"/index.php/51_AC\" title=\"51 AC\">51&#160;AC</a>, after an attempted assassination of Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Alysanne_Targaryen\" title=\"Alysanne Targaryen\">Alysanne Targaryen</a> at the sacred waters known as <a href=\"/index.php/Jonquil%27s_Pool\" title=\"Jonquil&#39;s Pool\">Jonquil's Pool</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/Maidenpool\" title=\"Maidenpool\">Maidenpool</a>, it was decided that the queen needed a protector who could accompany her where men couldn't go. Jaehaerys sent a raven to <a href=\"/index.php/Duskendale\" title=\"Duskendale\">Duskendale</a>, commanding the new Lord <a href=\"/index.php/House_Darklyn\" title=\"House Darklyn\">Darklyn</a> to send his bastard half-sister to court. Jonquil arrived in <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> a few days later, and gladly accepted the position of Queen Alysanne's <a href=\"/index.php/Sworn_shield\" title=\"Sworn shield\">sworn shield</a> and protector. In time she became known as the <i>Scarlet Shadow</i>, so closely did she guard her lady.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabbirth.2C_death_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabbirth.2C_death_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Queen_Alysanne_and_Jonquil_Darke_by_chillyravenart.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/9/93/Queen_Alysanne_and_Jonquil_Darke_by_chillyravenart.jpg/350px-Queen_Alysanne_and_Jonquil_Darke_by_chillyravenart.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"300\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/9/93/Queen_Alysanne_and_Jonquil_Darke_by_chillyravenart.jpg/525px-Queen_Alysanne_and_Jonquil_Darke_by_chillyravenart.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/9/93/Queen_Alysanne_and_Jonquil_Darke_by_chillyravenart.jpg/700px-Queen_Alysanne_and_Jonquil_Darke_by_chillyravenart.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Queen_Alysanne_and_Jonquil_Darke_by_chillyravenart.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Alysanne and Jonquil, by Chillyravenart</div></div></div>\n<p>When the <a href=\"/index.php/High_Lickspittle\" title=\"High Lickspittle\">High Septon</a> passed away in <a href=\"/index.php/54_AC\" title=\"54 AC\">54&#160;AC</a>, Jaehaerys and Alysanne traveled to <a href=\"/index.php/Oldtown\" title=\"Oldtown\">Oldtown</a> upon their <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragons</a> to pay their respects, and to influence the choice of the next <a href=\"/index.php/High_Septon\" title=\"High Septon\">High Septon</a>. They took two protectors with them. To balance the weight for the dragons, Jonquil rode with King Jaehaerys on <a href=\"/index.php/Vermithor\" title=\"Vermithor\">Vermithor</a>, while Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Joffrey_Doggett\" title=\"Joffrey Doggett\">Joffrey Doggett</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\">Kingsguard</a> rode with Alysanne on <a href=\"/index.php/Silverwing\" title=\"Silverwing\">Silverwing</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabbirth.2C_death_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabbirth.2C_death_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Jonquil traveled with Queen Alysanne when she went on a <a href=\"/index.php/Progress\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Progress\">progress</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/North\" title=\"North\">North</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_58_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">58&#160;AC</a>. A small <a href=\"/index.php/Tourney\" title=\"Tourney\">tourney</a> was staged in <a href=\"/index.php/White_Harbor\" title=\"White Harbor\">White Harbor</a> by <a href=\"/index.php/House_Manderly\" title=\"House Manderly\">House Manderly</a> in the queen's honor. One of the competitors was a <a href=\"/index.php/Wildling\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Wildling\">wildling</a> woman, captured by <a href=\"/index.php/Night%27s_Watch\" title=\"Night&#39;s Watch\">Night's Watch</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Rangers\" title=\"Rangers\">rangers</a> north of the <a href=\"/index.php/Wall\" title=\"Wall\">Wall</a>, and given to one of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Theomore_Manderly\" title=\"Theomore Manderly\">Theomore Manderly</a>'s knights to <a href=\"/index.php/Foster\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Foster\">foster</a>. Impressed with the woman's daring, Alysanne had Jonquil spar with her. The two women dueled with sword and spear, while the northmen roared with approval. <sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>When the scandals committed by Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Saera_Targaryen\" title=\"Saera Targaryen\">Saera Targaryen</a> came to light in <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_84_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">84&#160;AC</a>, and the young princess was confined to her room only to later attempt to escape to the <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonpit\" title=\"Dragonpit\">Dragonpit</a>, the king confined Saera to a tower cell, with Jonquil guarding her all day and night, even in the privy. When King Jaehaerys faced one of Saera's lovers, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Braxton_Beesbury\" title=\"Braxton Beesbury\">Braxton Beesbury</a>, in a <a href=\"/index.php/Trial_by_combat\" title=\"Trial by combat\">trial by combat</a>, Jonquil made sure Saera watched from the window of her cell as her father slew him with <a href=\"/index.php/Blackfyre\" title=\"Blackfyre\">Blackfyre</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Behind_the_Scenes\">Behind the Scenes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Jonquil_Darke&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Behind the Scenes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Jonquil Darke's name may be a reference to the warrior maiden <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joan_of_Arc\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Joan of Arc\">Joan of Arc</a> (<i>Jeanne d'Arc</i> in <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/French_langauge\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:French langauge\">French</a>). The similarities do end there since Joan was a peasant and not a noble bastard and did not actually fight herself but served as a rallying point carrying a banner, and was also a religious figure which Jonquil is not.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Jonquil_Darke&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, The Year of the Three Brides - 49 AC.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabbirth.2C_death_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabbirth.2C_death_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabbirth.2C_death_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\">2.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabbirth.2C_death_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\">2.2</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, Birth, Death and Betrayal Under King Jaehaerys I.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, Jaehaerys and Alysanne - Their Triumphs and Tragedies.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, The Long Reign - Jaehaerys and Alysanne: Policy, Progeny, and Pain.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260403181924\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.100 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.317 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 1199/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 10797/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 10529/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 2764/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 12/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 4352/5000000 bytes\nLua time usage: 0.200/7.000 seconds\nLua virtual size: 6.52 MB/50 MB\nLua estimated memory usage: 0 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%  300.199      1 -total\n 90.25%  270.929      1 Template:Infobox_character\n 89.82%  269.627      1 Template:Infobox\n 12.55%   37.665     12 Template:Infobox_value\n  5.49%   16.472      5 Template:Infobox_label\n  5.48%   16.439      8 Template:Ref\n  5.02%   15.064      5 Template:Date\n  3.39%   10.166      8 Template:Ref/core\n  0.91%    2.730      1 Template:References\n  0.35%    1.063      2 Template:Main_other\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key westeros_awoiaftest-mw_:pcache:idhash:25031-0!canonical and timestamp 20260403181924 and revision id 327226\n -->\n",
